  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigeria - Hunger Crisis 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">200,000 people</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is reported1 that in North West Nigeria, 2.53 million people are projected to face acute food insecurity (Phase 3 and above) in June &#x2013; August 2021 lean period. An estimated five percent of the total food insecure population (138,476 individuals) are internally displaced persons (IDPs), of which 26,000 are in the emergency acute food insecurity phase (CH phase 4). Zamfara North, Katsina Central and Katsina South are projected to be in Crisis phase between June and August 2021.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigeria</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The North East Nigeria has a high level of food insecurity affected by long running armed conflict and violence. Nigeria&#x2019;s North West region &#x2013; particularly states of Zamfara, Sokoto, and Katsina &#x2013; has in recent years seen a deterioration in the security situation, marked by an increase in banditry and violence</narrative>
  </description>
